<h1>DDoS Attack</h1>

<h3>Definition</h3>
<p>A Distributed Denial of Service attack overwhelms a server using multiple systems.</p>

<h3>How It Works</h3>
<ol>
<li>Attacker builds botnet.</li>
<li>Botnet sends traffic flood.</li>
<li>Server resources exhausted.</li>
<li>Service becomes unavailable.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Real-World Example</h3>
<p>GitHub DDoS attack in 2018 via memcached amplification.</p>

<h3>Diagram</h3>
<div class="border p-4 text-center">[Diagram Placeholder]</div>

<h3>Impact</h3>
<ul>
<li>Website downtime</li>
<li>Financial loss</li>
<li>Reputation damage</li>
</ul>

<h3>Prevention</h3>
<ul>
<li>Use CDN</li>
<li>Enable rate limiting</li>
<li>Deploy firewall</li>
</ul>

<h3>Educational Tools Used</h3>
<p>LOIC (educational research only)</p>

<h3>Safety Tips</h3>
<p>Never attempt attacks without authorization.</p>

